        "summary": "## Goal\n1. Diagnose and fix recurring 5:30 AM Morning Brief cron job timeouts\n2. Ensure all cron jobs run reliably\n3. Complete full system/security audit\n4. Install Ollama for local models (deferred)\n5. Switch primary model from MiniMax to Grok for reliability\n6. Debug Agent Chat (built with Cody) â€” currently in progress\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Bobby wants minimal changes to cron job payloads (keep as default/same config)\n- No public exposure of services\n- All skills must be readable by Bobby\n- Keep MiniMax for chat sessions, Grok for automated cron jobs\n- No need to explain everything â€” just fix and confirm\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Diagnosed Morning Brief failures: MiniMax API cold-start stalls at ~65s, known OpenClaw issue #34487\n- [x] Replaced all failing cron jobs with fresh copies (MC Watchdog, Zyrtec, Flonase, Warm-Up, Morning Brief)\n- [x] Set all cron jobs to 3600s timeout\n- [x] Added 5:25 AM warm-up cron for Morning Brief\n- [x] Fixed all skill SKILL.md permissions (chmod 644 â€” were root-only: `rw-------`)\n- [x] Ran full security audit â€” gateway auth OK, no public exposure, FileVault ON, auto updates ON\n- [x] Fixed memory file missing: `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-07.md` created\n- [x] Deleted Morning Brief TEST cron (c51ba150)\n- [x] Switched all 8 cron jobs from `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7` to `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n- [x] Updated `agents.defaults.model.primary` to `grok-xai/grok-4.1-fast-non-reasoning`\n- [x] Rebuilt gateway after model switch\n- [x] Scheduled one-shot test for 9:50 PM tonight (auto-deletes after)\n- [x] Confirmed: Zyrtec, MC Watchdog, Nightly Intel, Flonase, Morning Brief all working with Grok\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Debugging Agent Chat (built with Cody) â€” not working when Bobby tries to use it. Location and specifics unclear.\n\n### Blocked\n- Ollama installation requires sudo (Bobby opted to skip for now)\n- Agent Chat location/details unclear â€” Bobby hasn't specified what's broken\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Grok primary / MiniMax fallback**: xAI Grok cold-starts ~1.3s vs MiniMax's 60+ seconds. Switched all cron jobs to Grok; per-agent chat sessions remain MiniMax.\n- **Fresh cron copies over edits**: Replaced broken crons entirely rather than patching â€” clean isolated sessions perform better.\n- **Warm-up ping at 5:25 AM**: Primes the isolated session before the 5:30 Morning Brief runs.\n- **Rex research**: Confirmed MiniMax issue is known OpenClaw bug #34487, no automatic retry for cron jobs (bug #24355).\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Debug Agent Chat**: Need Bobby to clarify what \"not working\" means â€” URL, error message, blank page, login failure, etc.\n2. **Test 9:50 PM tonight**: Confirm Grok-powered Morning Brief test delivers successfully\n3. **Tomorrow 5:30 AM**: Real test â€” Warm-Up (5:25) + Morning Brief (5:30) with Grok. Watch for success/failure.\n4. **Fix stale plugin config warnings**: `plugins.entries.all` and `plugins.allow: all` are stale entries in `openclaw.json` (not critical but visible on every command)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Cron IDs**:\n  - MC Watchdog: `4a078218-10ea-45b4-b42b-66bddea0bd0a`\n  - Morning Brief Warm-Up: `e63a926f-487e-4bbc-a626-cbf21b1b8670`\n  - Morning Brief: `0c8b1d5b-b2fd-45d4-b346-517699a1e000`\n  - Zyrtec Night: `0b1a15a2-bca1-4ae8-beeb-6fd4b3e2035c`\n  - Flonase Morning: `295537b1-3a90-436f-b7de-67d69a5347db`\n  - Nightly Intel: `b693b56a-babf-42a9-988c-0c0367840c23`\n  - Emmy Email Check: `d64702cd-150d-4b69-95b9-d1250b289efb`\n  - xfinity-credit-reminder: `cbcae1a9` (unknown origin, also switched to Grok)\n- **Files**:\n  - Skills: `~/.openclaw/skills/*/SKILL.md` (all now chmod 644)\n  - Config: `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (Grok set as primary)\n  - Cron jobs: `~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json` (all payloads updated to Grok)\n  - Mission Control logs: `~/.openclaw/logs/mission-control.err` (only Music.app errors, no agent-chat issues)\n  - Gateway logs: `~/.openclaw/logs/gateway.err.log`\n- **Mission Control**: Running at `http://localhost:8787` (works fine)\n- **Agent Chat project location**: Unknown â€” Bobby built it with Cody but location unclear. Searched `~/agent-mission-control/` (has recipe-rip, index.html) but no agent-chat found. SecondBrain/agent-inbox exists but is different.\n- **Stale config**: `openclaw.json` has `plugins.entries.all` and `plugins.allow: all` causing warnings on every command\n- **Morning Brief timeout pattern**: Exact 65-70 second timeout, input tokens only ~34k (vs 130-460k on successful runs), MiniMax API level failure, not config-level\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser (B G) is asking about an Agent Chat service that should be running at http://100.103.22.35:8788/.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant confirmed the service is accessible by curling the URL (got HTML response)\n- Initial `ps aux` check for processes didn't find a match via grep\n- Used `lsof` to check port 8788 directly, which revealed a **Node.js process (PID 22599)** listening on port 8788 with multiple established connections to Google processes (appears to be active browser sessions connecting to the service)\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe service **is running** and responsive. The Node process (owned by user `bobbygalletta`) has multiple active WebSocket-style connections, suggesting the service is in active use by connected clients.\n\n<read-files>\n/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md\n~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n~/.openclaw/skills/morning-brief/SKILL.md\n</read-files>",
