dded to Family Calendar\n- [x] **Morning Brief corrections from Bobby** (5:58 AM Apr 10):\n  - Taxes already done â†’ removed from reminders\n  - Amazon packages already picked up â†’ removed\n  - SuperGrok not needed â†’ removed from reminders\n  - Job search not needed (doing DoorDash) â†’ removed from reminders\n  - Xfinity already cancelled â†’ noted\n  - SuperGrok marked complete in Apple Reminders\n- [x] Bobby slept in until 11:15 AM Friday â€” missed 5 AM wake, 6 AM DoorDash, 9 AM Valvoline (called and still got in)\n- [x] Bobby woke up at 11:15 AM Friday and got Day 1 of full check-in coverage\n- [x] **Active Memory plugin** in OpenClaw 2026.4.10 â€” dedicated memory sub-agent runs before every reply, pulls relevant preferences/context automatically\n- [x] **OpenClaw updated 2026.4.9 â†’ 2026.4.10** â€” gateway restarted; new features: Active Memory, Codex provider, MLX speech (macOS Talk Mode), Seedance 2.0 video generation\n- [x] Bobby confirmed: taxes done, Easter celebrated with Logan, Amazon packages picked up, SuperGrok not needed, job search not needed (DD), Xfinity cancelled\n- [x] **Bills updated**: Cap One + Discover + GEICO + Affirm all on Family Calendar; Tax Day April 15 noted ($237.25 total)\n- [x] Bobby's DD new goal: **$164/day** (previously $162)\n- [x] **Patriot Bonds** noted as emergency backup financial resource\n- [x] Bobby tried Telegram live location sharing â€” live location message (id: 22073) in Telegram thread; tried to set up automatic \"text when home\" notification\n- [x] Location-based reminder test: cron (id: `97d21697-2571-4eee-84b1-775c75fb9d43`) created every 3 min to check message 22073; **cron could not reliably fetch Telegram message by ID** â†’ false positive \"testing location\" sent too early; cron deleted; Bobby frustrated with spam\n- [x] Bobby asked me to always reference message 22073 for location; I committed to checking it when needed without asking him to resend\n- [x] **Agent-to-agent communication tested succ